  						<table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF AGGRESSIVE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;60</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;3 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;27 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;27 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>The warrior will do more damage with every blow landed but will also take more damage as well. This discipline lasts for 3 minutes and has a base reuse time of 27 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>RUIN</span><b>, By Rhaziitz</b> <small>(6/1/2001)</small><br><br>Well it sounds like a good dmg overall discipline, but something you should ALL know is that when an Enchanter casts ruin on you he automatically becomes the BIGGEST taunt in game.  Which will mean he will die, trust me i have seen it.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>EVERQUEST IS NOT SOLOQUEST</span><b>, By Irongrip of innoruuk</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>This and the other Disciplines are melee vs melee due to the fact that a Warrior is not going to be soloing at level 60.  Go into OlD Sebilis, HS, VP, or Chardok and you'll find that you need a Cleric, Evacer/back-up healer, Pet Class/ Blaster, Enchanter, and 2 tanks-one of which is taunt based.  Warrior's are the steal vs steal and are designed to be buffed by their group members so they can be effective at it.  This disciple is designed to allow the Warrior a greater advantage if you use your head and plan it correctly.<P>
     Have your Enchanter cast Rune and Augment on you.  Then as you use your disciple have him cast a berserker spell like Bedlam.  The Augment makes up for lost agi and gives you an extra amount of Damage absorbance.  Throughout the battle the Enchanter (if he has the crowd under control) can continue casting the berserk spell for lessened damage taken.<P>  
     Using the above your taunt factor increases, your damage increases, and the mob your killing dies faster.  This is also helpful in cases where the mob has a high magic resist rendering your casters helpless.  Also, any Cleric at this level has learned to adjust their healing factors to fit the given situation.  In PvP situations I see this as unhelpfull, but I don't play PvP for these types of reasons.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>IMP</span><b>, By Imp</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>What you aren't looking at is the exponential factor of this dicipline.  The point is to do exponential damage. It's not 'oh I will do x more damage per hit, but my damage per hit will increase By x, so if I do 2 damage the first hit I would do 4 the next hit then 8 the next hit, That adds up extremely fast, and likewise you take (rumor0 exponential damage. I see it as a last ditch effort to do so much damage. <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>HMM....</span><b>, By Commenter</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I assume that you are using Nagafen as a theoretical encounter, since lvl 60's are too high to attack him.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>A COMMENT.</span><b>, By Just</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I think you guys aren't thinking of tactics here, lets see a group has 6 people, a nagafen group has 20. Its not like you are going to be the target all of the time, unless of course you are already doing the most damage, so lets say you are at naga, hes beeting on fighter # 1, not you # 2, so you figure hell, im not getting hit, lets dish out some extra beats. so now your hitting for extra damage , naga is hitting #1, and youre happy, when naga switches to you , #1 can use his special to get its attention again, mean while , fighters 3 4 5 6 7 can all be doing this too, I dont think you guys are thinking of the tactical advantages here, this game is certainly not ment to be one on one, so why are you looking at it that way??<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
